<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <title>About Eduexchange</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #F2F0EF; /* Light background color */
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            width: 100%;
            background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
            padding: 30px 55px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 5px 20px #351E10; /* Box shadow */
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }

        .container:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px); /* Slight hover effect */
        }

        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 35px;
            color: #351E10;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .content {
            text-align: left;
        }

        .content h2 {
            font-size: 22px;
            color: #351E10;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .content p {
            font-size: 16px;
            color: #351E10;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        /* Responsive adjustments */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                padding: 15px; /* Reduce overall padding for smaller screens */
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    
    <div class="container">
        <h1>About Us</h1>
        
        <div class="content">
            <h2>Welcome to Eduexchange</h2>
            <p>Welcome to Eduexchange,the go-to marketplace for engineering students to buy, sell used textbooks! At Eduexchange, we understand the challenges students face in acquiring quality educational resources on a budget. That’s why we’re dedicated to creating a platform that connects engineering students with affordable textbooks, ensuring knowledge remains accessible and budget-friendly.</p>

            <p>Our mission is simple, to make education more accessible by providing a sustainable way for students to buy and sell their textbooks. By creating a circular economy for textbooks, we’re helping students save money, reduce waste, and foster a collaborative learning environment.</p>
            
            <p>Whether you’re starting your first semester or completing your final project, Eduexchange is here to support you every step of the way. Join our community of students who are changing the way we think about textbooks. Let's make learning more affordable and sustainable together!</p>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
